result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (5th or 6th) [Modifiers: Alcohol Fine Enhancer] and Operating w/ PAC (5th or 6th) [Modifiers: Alcohol Fine Enhancer]. The defendant was found guilty of OWI (5th or 6th) [Modifiers: Alcohol Fine Enhancer] and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC (5th or 6th) [Modifiers: Alcohol Fine Enhancer] was dismissed by the court.

  • Frank T Dingena was found guilty of OWI (5th or 6th) [Modifiers: Alcohol Fine Enhancer], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Frank T Dingena in court with attorney Jeffrey John Szczewski.  Brian J. Juech appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 1.  Court finds defendant guilty.  Count 2 dismissed by operation of law.  Recommendations by the State.  Arguments by the Defense.  Statement by S.D.  Statements by defendant.

Court orders the following: 
- Total sentence: 5 years 6 months (Initial Confinement: 2 years 6 months, Extended Supervision: 3 years).  Credit for 366 days.
- Defendant IS NOT eligible for Challenge Incarceration
- Defendant IS eligible for Substance Abuse Program
- 36 months Drivers License Revocation. 
- 36 months Ignition Interlock on every vehicle TITLED OR REGISTERED to defendant
- Attendance at a Victim Impact Panel meeting while on Extended Supervision
- Alcohol Assessment
- Court costs waived. 
- Blood Test Reimbursement of $60.00 paid through Waukesha County Circuit Court to be forwarded to Menomonee Falls Police Department
- DNA Surcharge waived.
- DNA Sample waived.
- Conditions of Extended Supervision:  Maintain absolute sobriety/Random UAs.  No use or possession of alcohol/drug paraphernalia/drugs without a valid prescription.  Attend a minimum of 2 self help meetings per week and obtain a sponsor within 1 month of release.  
Defendant was remanded to the custody of the Sheriff to commence the sentence.
Plea/sentencing hearing on June 10, 2015 at 09:30 am.
